  "prompt": "Which \"is\" the best pair of in-ear earphones under Rs. 1000?",
  "response": "Okay, finding the \"best\" under Rs. 1000 is subjective, as sound preference varies. However, based on common recommendations, reviews, and overall value, here are a few of the *most popular and well-regarded* in-ear earphones in that price range (in India, assuming you're referring to the Indian Rupee):\n\n**Top Recommendations:**\n\n*   **boAt Bassheads 225:** A classic choice. Known for its bass-heavy sound signature and durability. Widely available. Usually the go-to recommendation for bass lovers.  It is available with both 3.5mm and type-c connectors.\n*   **realme Buds Classic:**  Good all-around performance.  Decent sound quality and comfortable fit for many.\n\n**Other Good Options (depending on availability and deals):**\n\n*   **Boult Audio ZCharge:** Claims extremely fast charging. Good sound.\n*   **Mivi ThunderBeats 2:** Known for its bass performance and noise isolation.\n*   **Philips SHE1505BK/94:** A budget friendly basic option from a trustworthy brand.\n\n**Factors to Consider When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Sound Signature:**  Do you prefer balanced, bass-heavy, or neutral sound?\n*   **Comfort & Fit:** In-ear earphones come with different ear tip sizes. Make sure they fit snugly and comfortably in your ears for the best sound isolation and listening experience.\n*   **Durability:** Consider the build quality and cable quality, especially if you'll be using them frequently.\n*   **Features:**  Mic for calls, in-line controls (volume, play/pause), noise isolation, etc.  Decide which features are important to you.\n*   **Availability:** Some models may be easier to find than others in your local stores or online.\n\n**Why No Single \"Best\"?**\n\n*   **Personal Preference:** What sounds good to one person might not sound good to another.\n*   **Constantly Evolving Market:** New models are released frequently, and prices fluctuate.\n*   **Counterfeit Products:** Be wary of fake products, especially when buying online. Buy from reputable sellers.\n\n**Recommendations Before Buying:**\n\n1.  **Read Reviews:** Check online reviews on sites like Amazon, Flipkart, tech blogs, and YouTube.\n2.  **Consider Your Use Case:** Are these for gym use, commuting, calls, or just general music listening?\n3.  **Check for Deals:** Prices can vary significantly, so shop around.\n\nGood luck with your search!\n",
